mainEntity.name: What is the JAC Delhi Counselling registration process at IGDTUW?

acceptedAnswer.text: The JAC Delhi Counselling 2023 process starts with online registration. Mentioned below is the step-wise JAC Delhi Registration process: Step 1: JAC Delhi Counselling Authentication - Candidates have to authenticate themselves using the details like JEE Main 2023 application number, Name as per JEE Main 2023 admit card, Date of birth as per JEE Main application. Once the aforementioned details match successfully, candidates are asked to enter their email id and mobile number. A verification code is sent to the mobile number and thereafter candidates can enter a password of their choice. Candidates have to use the JEE Main application number and password for logging into the JAC Delhi portal whenever needed. Step 2: JAC Delhi Counselling Filling the application form - Once the authentication is done, candidates have to fill in the application form carefully with all details asked. Further candidates are required to upload the scanned documents in the online application form. The scanned documents must be as per the format indicated in the online form. Step 3: JAC Delhi Counselling Payment of the Application Fee - Candidates have to pay the counselling/ application fee. The mode of application fee payment is credit card/ debit card/ net banking. Step 4: JAC Delhi Counselling Form printout - As a final step, candidates must take the printout of the form. This printout is to be submitted to the reporting institute.

mainEntity.name: I have 23027 rank in JEE Mains along with 3253 EWS rank. Can I get admission for CSE with bioscience in IIIT Delhi?

acceptedAnswer.text: As seen last year, IIIT Delhi implemented a bonus system where a certain number of bonus points will be added as per specific achievements to your percentile score of JEE Mains. For getting CSE, bonus points are required as a person with 6000 AIR, and 2 Bonus points got CSE in IIITD while a person with 600 AIR who was getting CSE in IIIT Hyderabad did not get CSE in IIIT Delhi because of no bonus points. (For, e. g. if you get even 99.95 %ile in JEE Mains, a person with 98percentile but with two bonus points will be evaluated at a score of 100 (98 + 2) and will be placed above the 99.95%iler in the merit list).
